<P>A HERMIT'S TALE: RECORDED BY HIS OWN HAND, AND FOUND IN HIS CELL.</P>
<Q><L>There oft is found an Avarice in Grief;</L>
<L>And the wan Eye of Sorrow loves to gaze</L>
<L>Upon the &s;ecret Hoard of trea&s;ur'd Woes.</L>
<BIBL>MASON.</BIBL></Q>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI> PRINTED FOR T. CADELL, IN THE STRAND. M.DCC.LXXXVII.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="dedication">
<PB REF="2">
<HEAD>RICHARD BRINSLEY SHERIDAN, E&s;q.</HEAD>
<OPENER><SALUTE>SIR,</SALUTE></OPENER>
<P>EQUALLY induced by a ju&s;t admiration of your talents, and a grateful &s;en&s;e of the di&s;tinction your prai&s;e has given to tho&s;e you were plea&s;ed to find in me, permit me to &s;olicit your further indulgence to this little production; and be a&s;&s;ured, its greate&s;t value in my eyes is, that it &s;erves to convey tho&s;e ac|knowledgments, with which I have the honour to remain,</P>
<CLOSER><SALUTE>SIR,</SALUTE> <SIGNED>Your mo&s;t obliged, Obedient humble &s;ervant,
SOPHIA LEE.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
